    http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/Common/v4

    ValueWithAttributes RateRange

      • http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/Common/v4:RateRange

      • Description

        A range of monetary values within which the cost of the available products are requested.

    • Example XML

      <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>

<RateRange currencyCode="USD" fixedRate="100.0000" maxRate="100.0000" minRate="100.0000" rateTimeUnit="Day" xmlns="http://www.opentravel.org/OTM/Common/v4"/>

      Example JSON

      {
  "RateRange" : {
    "value" : null,
    "minRate" : 100.0000,
    "maxRate" : 100.0000,
    "fixedRate" : 100.0000,
    "rateTimeUnit" : "Day",
    "currencyCode" : "USD"
  }
}

      • Attribute Summary

        Attributes 
        Name Description
        minRate
        A decimal value that indicates the minimum monetary value to be considered in a request for an available product.
        Details
        Type Money
        Example Value 100.00
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        maxRate
        A decimal value that indicates the maximum monetary value to be considered in a request for an available product.
        Details
        Type Money
        Example Value 100.00
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        fixedRate
        The rate amount used in place of MinRate and MaxRate when a specific rate is being requested.
        Details
        Type Money
        Example Value 100.00
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        rateTimeUnit
        Used to specify the period of time to which the rates apply.
        Details
        Type TimeUnit_Enum
        Example Value Day
        Required false
        Pattern N/A
        Max Occurrences 1
        currencyCode
        An ISO 4217 (3) alpha character code that specifies a monetary unit.
        Details
        Type CurrencyCode_ISO4217
        Example Value USD
        Required false
        Pattern [a-zA-Z]{3}
        Max Occurrences 1
